eges and universities. Who's going to pay for that? Unfortu�nately, Madam\nSpeaker, it's going to be students. ","index":"00256","speaker":""},{"html":"����� Will\nthis minister explain to this House, but, more importantly, to students and\ntheir families, why he's underfunding universities and colleges and forcing\nstudents to pay more? <i>[interjection]</i>� ","index":"00257","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Madam\nSpeaker:</b> Order. Order. ","index":"00258","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Hon.\nWayne </b><b><a name=\"_Toc69280242\">Ewasko</a></b><b>�(Minister\nof Advanced Education, Skills and Immigration):</b> We know here&nbsp; in\nManitoba�we believe, on this side of the House�working with our post-secondary\npartners. That includes our post-secondary institutions, our students, our\nfaculty members, all our partners, all across the whole board. ","index":"00259","speaker":"Wayne Ewasko"},{"html":"����� We,\nonce again, Madam Speaker, are funding post-secondary institutions over\n$1&nbsp;billion of direct and indirect funding once again. ","index":"00260","speaker":""},{"html":"����� I wish\nthis member would get on side and stop fear‑mongering Manitoba students\nand taxpayers, Madam Speaker. ","index":"00261","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Madam\nSpeaker:</b> The honourable member for St.&nbsp; Vital, on a supplementary\nquestion. ","index":"00262","speaker":""},{"html":"<b>Mr.\nMoses:</b> Bill 33 gives the minister full control over tuition, the ability to\noverride funding decisions made by administration, faculty and student leader�ship.\nThe reality is that this minister will continue to cut college and university\nfunding, force tuition up, while also giving him the power to block proposals and\nimprovements that come out of student leader�ship.","index":"00263","speaker":"Jamie Moses"},{"html":"����� The\nminister is�says he is proposing an amend�ment to this bill, but will he\nfinally be clear ","index":"00264","speaker":""},{"html":"����� Will\nhe allow students to se